          <h2>Capture ideas easily</h2>
          <p>MindMup tries very hard to make idea capture as frictionless as possible. 
          Powerful keyboard shortcuts enable you to focus on presentation content instead of menus. Just drag images
          from your file system and drop on the nodes to add pictures to text.</p>
          <a class="btn btn-default" href="/keyboard-shortcuts" role="button">More info »</a>
        </div>
        <div class="feature col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          <img class="img-circle col-header" src="/img/presentations/drag_into_sboard_500.png">
          <h2>Build a storyboard</h2>
          <p>Simply drag and drop mind map nodes to the storyboard pane to organise your presentation. Create bullet points easily by adding
          a node with its children into the storyboard.
          The storyboard automatically updates when you change node contents.
          </p>
          <a class="btn btn-default" href="/storyboards#starting" role="button">More info »</a>
        </div>
        <div class="feature col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          <img class="img-circle col-header" src="/img/presentations/slides_500.png">
          <h2>Make beautiful slides</h2>
          <p>Turn the storyboard into beautiful PDF slides with just one click. MindMup will format node images and text into 4x3 aspect ratio slides
          that look great on all projectors, automatically choosing the best font size. Slides are vectors so they will also print nicely.</p>
          <a class="btn btn-default" href="/storyboards#exporting" role="button">More info »</a>
        </div>
        <div class="feature col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          <img class="img-circle col-header" src="/img/presentations/powerpoint_500.png">
